---
Scarab-beetle folk of the desert whose origin myths trace to the Great Scarab's passage
through the earth, the Khephari are ancient, unhurried, and constitutionally tuned to
the desert's cyclic timescale. They built the approach roads to the Great Pyramid during
the Solar Court Era and continue to quietly maintain the route markers their ancestors
set. Khephari communities near the Cinderteeth Mountains serve as seismic early-warning
systems, detecting volcanic activity through vibration-sense long before other peoples
notice a thing — warnings which human institutions have consistently received and filed
without action.
